title: Indent with tabs, align with spaces
description: Tabs vs. spaces for whitespace: which to use? Tabs are good for indentation because their width can be adjusted according to preference (:help 'tabstop'). On the other hand, spaces must be used to ensure text stays lined up across lines if tabstop is changed. Using the "smart tabs" scheme described below combines the strengths of both. This tip discusses indenting using tabs and spaces, including methods to allow tabstop adjustment, while maintaining textual alignment. See indenting source code
